        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 5:29PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 527 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a thunderstorm 23 miles
west of Big Sandy, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and brief heavy rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Additionally, minor flooding could occur in areas that received
heavy rainfall earlier this afternoon.

Locations impacted include...
Havre, Big Sandy, Azure, Parker School, Beaver Creek, Agency, St.
Pierre, Sangrey, Boneau, Box Elder, Rocky Boy, Laredo, and
Kenilworth.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Brief heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
